This LoRA is based on Lance Bass during the 2000's. Think frosted blond tips and spiky and gelled hair.

In the early 2000s, Lance Bass was a prominent figure in the entertainment world as a member of the hugely successful boy band NSYNC. Known for his distinctive bass voice and boyish charm, Lance and NSYNC released hit albums like "No Strings Attached" (2000) and "Celebrity" (2001), with chart-topping singles such as "Bye Bye Bye" and "It's Gonna Be Me."

Beyond music, Lance Bass ventured into acting with appearances on TV shows like "7th Heaven" and became a pop culture icon. His public coming out as gay in 2006 made him a notable LGBTQ+ advocate, and he also engaged in philanthropic efforts and business ventures during this period, leaving a lasting mark on the early 2000s entertainment landscape.

items.name: EYE SEE YOU
items.description:
English/ä¸­æ–‡

Is that an eye? It gazes at me through the hole in the wall, and as I look deeper, the eye blinks and disappears into the darkness. There's still something looking at me, and when I turn my head, I see those eyes. The pictures on the wall, the books on the shelf, the vase on the table, all sprout eyes. Black, red, blue, they silently stare at me, conveying some mysterious message.

I cannot believe what I am seeing, and crazy thoughts fill my mind. I close my eyes, hoping that this eerie sight will vanish. But when I open my eyes again, the number of eyes has increased, and their gaze has become more intense.

Fear drives me to flee the apartment. I see that giant eye! It hangs among the clouds, emitting a terrifying aura. The pupil of that eye is unfathomably deep, as if it can devour everything. It silently stares at me, revealing an indescribable power in its gaze.

Suddenly, the giant eye slowly closes. Before its eyelids completely shut, everything around me gradually disappears.

The eye is now completely closed.

This LoRA takes inspiration from gaze and can add eyes to any object or even the sky, creating highly artistic and surreal images.

Instructions:

  • Recommended trigger words: (objects) with (color) ceyes

  • Weight: 0.7-1

  • Positive prompt words: realistic, no human,

  • Negative prompt words: easynegative, painting, human, man, woman, girl, boy, manuscript,

  • Recommended models: cyberrealistic_v31 (This LoRA is based on training with SD1.5, so it can be applied to most checkpoints based on SD1.5. Different checkpoints may produce slightly different results.)

  • Example image generation parameters: Steps: 20, Sampler: DPM++ 2M SDE Karras, CFG scale: 7, Size: 512x768, Denoising strength: 0.5, Clip skip: 2, Hires upscale: 2, Hires upscaler: R-ESRGAN 4x+. (Hires upscaler effect is not necessary but still produces good results)

Creating this LoRA has taken a lot of effort, and I hope to receive more comments and feedback, as well as images created using this model. If you have any questions or suggestions regarding this LoRA, please feel free to contact me. I look forward to your feedback!

items.name: Clayanim
items.description:
Here's a LoRa based on clay animation films.

Quite simple to use, it can still sometimes give you strange results... :-)

Warning: don't use negative prompts like bad drawn, bad art, etc. They'll take away everything that makes this LoRa so special.

Works great with Realistic Vision - but also with others ;-)

Warning for SDXL version. This is a Lycoris because I only have a 8go VRAM card and this is the only way to do a training SDXL. And you have to follow this :

  • Don't use negative prompts like bad drawn, bad art, etc. They'll take away everything that makes this LoRa so special.

  • Don't use refiner : it's softens the details too much

  • if the result is "too photorealistic" and doesn't seem to be what's expected, you should add "miniature" to your prompt

Have fun!
